# DataTableToolbar — Slot Naming Convention

When someone refers to the **"filter slot"** on `DataTableToolbar`, they mean the **`#saved-views`** slot. This is the area in the **left group** of the toolbar, positioned **right after the Filter button** (and after search/quick filters).

Use this slot to place custom inline content such as record counts, labels, or any additional information next to the Filter button.

## Toolbar Layout Reference

```
[Left group]                                                    [Right group]
[+ Add] [🔍 Search] [Quick Filters] [#saved-views] [Filter]    [↻ Refresh] [Columns] [⬇ Export]
```

## Available Slots

| Slot Name | Position | Use For |
|---|---|---|
| `#saved-views` | Left group — after search/quick filters, before Filter button | **"Filter slot"** — custom inline content like record counts, labels, view selectors, checkboxes |
| `#column-config` | Right group — between Refresh and Export buttons | Custom column config content |
| `#export` | Right group — rightmost position | Custom export/download content |
| `#below-toolbar` | Below the entire toolbar row | Content that spans the full toolbar width |

## Example — Adding a Record Count Next to Filter

```html
<DataTableToolbar
  addButtonLabel="Add SSO App"
  searchPlaceholder="Search"
  :showAddButton="true"
  :showRefreshButton="true"
  :showDownloadButton="true"
>
  <template #saved-views>
    <span class="text-body-md text-neutral-subtle">75 Applications</span>
  </template>
</DataTableToolbar>
```
